comments: Murray (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact created by Westbrook (WAS) during his post play at the basket. Westbrook makes a natural basketball move and does not extend his forearm out or deliver contact to dislodge Murray.
At the end of the drive, Beal (WAS) places a resting hand on DeRozan's (SAS) body and marginal contact occurs that does not affect DeRozan's ability to make his intended pass.
During the baseline cut, Poeltl (SAS) and Bertans (WAS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
DeRozan (SAS) stops his forward momentum and releases from the contact with Beal (WAS) at the end of his drive.
DeRozan (SAS) runs alongside of and absorbs the contact created by Westbrook (WAS) on his driving shot attempt.
Bertans (WAS) moves from A to B into and makes contact with DeRozan's (SAS) body after the release, which affects his ability to follow through naturally on his jump shot attempt.
After the pick, Len (WAS) starts his roll to the basket and marginal contact occurs as he engages and disengages with Murray (SAS).
DeRozan (SAS) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position while absorbing the contact during the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
Westbrook (WAS) legally contests DeRozan's (SAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

Murray (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact created by Beal (WAS) during his driving shot attempt. Johnson (SAS) make clean ball contact and avoids any contact to Beal's arm on his dislodge attempt.
During the rebound, Len (WAS) and Poeltl (SAS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Beal (WAS) dislodges Mills (SAS) from his legal guarding position.
Poeltl (SAS) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Beal (WAS).
Poeltl (SAS) is established in Len's (WAS) path and does not use his arms to restrict Len's FOM or ability to defend the shot.
Hachimura (WAS) firms up on his right foot and marginal contact occurs with Johnson (SAS) during his driving shot attempt.

Murray (SAS) extends his arm through the dribble hand-off and makes clean ball contact to deflect the pass away from Beal (WAS). Any contact between Beal and Murray as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Westbrook's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact as Westbrook fights over the pick.
Westbrook (WAS) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs to Murray's (SAS) arm at the end of the drive, which does not affect his ability to maintain his dribble and gather.
Mills (SAS) engages on the pick and marginal contact occurs with Bertans (WAS) as he switches defensively. The reaction by Bertans is not commensurate with the level of contact.

Johnson (SAS) and DeRozan (SAS) both pursue the rebound and make clean ball contact as they try to catch the ball. Any contact with Hachimura's (WAS) head as Johnson is attempting to retrieve the ball is deemed incidental. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Before Beal (WAS) or Westbrook (WAS) make ball contact to tie it up, DeRozan (SAS) is granted his timeout request.
A timeout request is granted before any marginal body contact between Bertans (WAS) and DeRozan (SAS).
Westbrook (WAS) makes contact with DeRozan's (SAS) arm/elbow and the contact affects his intended pass.
Bertans (WAS) commits a take foul on Mills (SAS).
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Beal's (WAS) jump shot attempt and any foot to foot contact after the release is deemed incidental as it is a result of Beal extending his leg out to the right.
